journal_entry: Shooting match all day in the evening to Christmas tree at the Hall.
The wind Southly and foggy hunting the Oxen to haul lumber for Wm. Dodge commenced to make side table
The wind south west went to Shooting match
The wind Northerly hunted all day for freight took up at night to go to Boston wrote letter to James Staples Lubec for a freight
The wind Northerly hunted all day for freight took up at night to go to Boston wrote letter to James Staples Lubec for a freight
The wind Westerly went on Grind Stone point hunting foxes with hounds
Wind very moderate all day N.N.W. Tood tug boat and towed to Calais at 10 AM. Hunted around the remainder of the day for a freight but could not find any.

Wind North West in morning hunted untill noon for a man to go a trip to New Bedford & got one. then wind South West, at 1 P.M. got underway at Winter Harbor and went out. At dark wind Westerly. and at 10 PM passed Mt Desert Rock Light midnight wind West North West So ends these 24 hours

Wind East North East Went on Grindstone point with Nicholas Bunker hunting foxes with a hound got none. In the afternoon helped Mr Farrows of Rockland take the Mlasure of the Sch Chromo for a suit of sails at the wharf Winter Harbor.
